c c --synthesis (wDNNF) regression: minimized from synth fuzzer seed
c c 816418904, test 152. Was a "no witness" failure caused by a brief
c c performance gate that consulted is_shareable(v) inside
c c synth_forced_lit. is_shareable reads shareable[], which is per
c c super-comp scratch and gets overwritten by nested
c c compute_shareable_vars calls -- by SAT-leaf time the array reflects
c c the innermost super-comp, not the ancestor where v was actually
c c shared across siblings. The gate then skipped the pin and the two
c c sibling SAT calls disagreed on var 12's polarity, producing an AND
c c node whose children share var 12 with both polarities (a wDNNF
c c violation). The fix gates on orig_polarity[v] -- a per-var,
c c initialize-time constant -- which gives the same perf benefit
c c without the staleness hazard.
c p show 1 2 3 4 0
c c RUN: %solver --compile %t.nnf --synthesis 1 %s
c c RUN: %ddnnf_verify %t.nnf --check-weak-decomposable
p cnf 12 3
11 -1 0
-5 12 -11 0
3 12 -9 0
